Inter Milan sporting director Piero Ausilio has admitted being left feeling ` sad ' after the club lost patience and decided to sell Philippe Coutinho to Liverpool .
The Brazil playmaker arrived at Anfield for just £ 8.5 million in 2013 and has a nomination for the PFA Player of the Year award .
Inter signed Coutinho as a teenager from Brazilian club Vasco de Gama before being sold for £ 855 m .